.TH "omap_device_assert_hardreset" 9 "omap_device_assert_hardreset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_device_assert_hardreset \- set a device's hardreset line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap_device_assert_hardreset
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
struct platform_device * to reset
.IP "name" 12
const char * name of the reset line
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the hardreset line identified by \fIname\fP on the IP blocks
associated with the hwmods backing the platform_device \fIpdev\fP.  All
of the hwmods associated with \fIpdev\fP must have the same hardreset
line linked to them for this to work.  Passes along the return value
of \fBomap_hwmod_assert_hardreset\fP in the event of any failure, or
returns 0 upon success.
